## 📋 Supplementary Notice

### Hardware Safety Warning

This project involves 18 high-current servos, Li-ion battery packs, and high-voltage power systems. When using this software to control hardware, please follow these safety guidelines:

1. **Battery Safety**: Always use a qualified BMS (Battery Management System) with Li-ion batteries to prevent overcharge, over-discharge, and short circuits.
2. **Power Safety**: The servo power circuit must include current-sharing resistors and filter capacitors. Never use a standard power adapter to drive multiple servos directly.
3. **Servo Protection**: Strictly adhere to the angle limits defined in the code. Mechanical stalling may cause servo burnout or equipment damage.
4. **Operating Environment**: Operate in a dry, static-free environment. Remove all batteries when not in use for extended periods.

> ⚠️ **Disclaimer**: The author assumes no liability for personal injury, equipment damage, or property loss resulting from failure to follow the above safety guidelines.

### Third-Party Services

This project utilizes the following third-party cloud services. You must obtain your own API keys before use:

| Service | Provider | Purpose | Apply At |
|---------|----------|---------|----------|
| Speech Recognition (STT) | Baidu AI Cloud | Speech-to-Text | https://ai.baidu.com |
| Speech Synthesis (TTS) | Baidu AI Cloud | Text-to-Speech | https://ai.baidu.com |
| LLM Conversation | Alibaba Cloud | AI Dialogue | https://www.aliyun.com |

- Fees, terms of service, and privacy policies for the above services are the sole responsibility of each provider.
- This repository contains **no valid API keys**. Replace them with your own before use.
- **Do not** upload code containing active API keys to public repositories.

### Chinese Font Library

The custom Chinese font library (`font_chinese.h`) included in this project was independently created by the author using bitmap generation tools. The font data is intended solely for use on this device's display. Please do not extract and use it in other commercial projects.

### 3D Printed Shell

If needed, STL model files for the shell are available in the `hardware/` directory of this repository. These files are also open-sourced under the MIT License and may be freely modified and printed.

### Derivative Works

Derivative projects based on this work are welcome! It is recommended to:

